<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Cylinder Head and Valves -
        Assemble - Assemble Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010405.3" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Assemble Valves</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate valve stems with clean engine oil and insert valves in valve guides.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate interior diameter of new valve stem seal assemblies with clean engine oil and
                install them over valve and valve guide as shown. Be sure seal assemblies are seated down against
                cylinder head spring pockets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010469" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5391.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install valve stem seal assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve spring over stem seal assembly. Be sure to install proper valve spring at
                proper valve location. Intake has orange paint marks and exhaust have white paint marks.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid damage to engine, keep intake and exhaust springs separate. Spring rates are
                        different and must not be mixed in cylinder head.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010470" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5200.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"/>
            <caption>Intake and Exhaust Valve Spring Comparison</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rotator assembly over valve spring.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Snap new rotator seals in bottom side (rotator cone) of valve rotators before installing
                        rotator assembly on engine.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010471" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5390.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install rotator assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress valve spring with
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_108.xml" xrefid="t210010405">Valve Spring Compressor (ZTSE1846)</hotlnk>
                and install spring locks.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010472" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5388.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install valve spring locks</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
